  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is correct. It&rsquo;s given that in a scale model, a length of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"1\"><mn>1</mn></math> inch is equivalent to a length of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"StartFraction 17 Over 3 EndFraction\"><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math> feet in the actual office building. This means that the ratio of a length, in feet, in the actual office building to the corresponding length, in inches, in the model is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"StartFraction 17 Over 3 EndFraction\"><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"1\"><mn>1</mn></math>. Therefore, the length, in inches, in the model corresponding to a length in the actual office building of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> feet can be found by dividing <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"StartFraction 17 Over 3 EndFraction\"><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>. Dividing by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"StartFraction 17 Over 3 EndFraction\"><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math> is equivalent to multiplying by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"three seventeenths\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>17</mn></mfrac></math>, so the corresponding length, in inches, in the model in terms of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> can be represented by the expression <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"StartFraction 3 x Over 17 EndFraction\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>17</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>\n<p>Choice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>\n<p>Choice D is incorrect. This expression represents the corresponding length, in inches, in the model in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> for a model where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"1\"><mn>1</mn></math> inch in the model is equivalent to a length of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"three seventeenths\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>17</mn></mfrac></math>, not <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"StartFraction 17 Over 3 EndFraction\"><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>, feet in the actual building.</p>",
